&lt;p&gt;commit 6a046d455bc521bd1da5a5f4ad64d4cb1a75a697&lt;br/&gt;
Author: Ryan Blue &amp;lt;blue@apache.org&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Date:   2015-05-28T22:46:44Z&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AVRO-1672&quot; title=&quot;Add logical types and conversions for date, time, and timestamp.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;AVRO-1672&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;AVRO-1672&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: Add time logical types and conversions.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    This uses Joda classes to represent the new logical types:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;date =&amp;gt; LocalDate&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;time-millis =&amp;gt; LocalTime&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;timestamp-millis =&amp;gt; DateTime&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;    Joda is an optional dependency and will only be loaded if the&lt;br/&gt;
    conversions in org.apache.avro.data.TimeConversions are referenced. By&lt;br/&gt;
    default, no logical type conversions are enabled so there is no&lt;br/&gt;
    additional runtime dependency for existing applications.&lt;/p&gt;

