            <title>[AVRO-1686] ENUM symbols are sorted by name in python3 implementation</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AVRO-1686</link>
                <project id="12310911" key="AVRO">Apache Avro</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In python3 EnumSchema class in schema.py doesn&apos;t preserve order of symbols which leads in total serialization/deserialization chaos.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;sample:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;import avro.schema&lt;br/&gt;
avro.schema.Parse(&apos;&lt;/p&gt;
{&quot;symbols&quot;: [&quot;IMPRESS&quot;, &quot;EVENTS&quot;, &quot;LAYOUT&quot;], &quot;type&quot;: &quot;enum&quot;, &quot;name&quot;: &quot;Type&quot;}
&lt;p&gt;&apos;).to_json()&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;returns:&lt;/p&gt;

{&apos;name&apos;: &apos;Type&apos;, &apos;symbols&apos;: (&apos;EVENTS&apos;, &apos;IMPRESS&apos;, &apos;LAYOUT&apos;), &apos;type&apos;: &apos;enum&apos;}
